TY  - JOUR
T1  - Semiparametric Estimation of a Proportional Hazard Model with Unobserved Heterogeneity
AU  - Horowitz, Joel L.
Y1  - 1999/09/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00068
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1001
EP  - 1028
VL  - 67
IS  - 5
KW  - Duration analysis
KW  - frailty
KW  - transformation model.
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00068
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - The proportional hazard model with unobserved heterogeneity gives the hazard function of a random variable conditional on covariates and a second random variable representing unobserved heterogeneity. This paper shows how to estimate the baseline hazard function and the distribution of the unobserved heterogeneity nonparametrically. The baseline hazard function and heterogeneity distribution are assumed to satisfy smoothness conditions but are not assumed to belong to known, finite-dimensional, parametric families. Existing estimators assume that the baseline hazard function or heterogeneity distribution belongs to a known parametric family. Thus, the estimators presented here are more general than existing ones.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - On the Existence of Pure and Mixed Strategy Nash Equilibria in Discontinuous Games
AU  - Reny, Philip J.
Y1  - 1999/09/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00069
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1029
EP  - 1056
VL  - 67
IS  - 5
KW  - Discontinuous games
KW  - better-reply security
KW  - payoff security
KW  - pure strategy
KW  - mixed strategy
KW  - Nash equilibrium
KW  - existence.
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00069
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - A game is better-reply secure if for every nonequilibrium strategy x* and every payoff vector limit u* resulting from strategies approaching x*, some player i has a strategy yielding a payoff strictly above ui* even if the others deviate slightly from x*. If strategy spaces are compact and convex, payoffs are quasiconcave in the owner's strategy, and the game is better-reply secure, then a pure strategy Nash equilibrium exists. Better-reply security holds in many economic games. It also permits new results on the existence of symmetric and mixed strategy Nash equilibria.
ER  - 

